https://github.com/alban-okoby/alx-system_engineering-devops/blob/master/0x09-web_infrastructure_design/alx_simple_web_infrastructure_design_okk.png

- The user's computer initiates the request.
- The DNS server resolves the domain name "www.foobar.com" to the IP address 8.8.8.8.
- The user's web browser sends an HTTP request to that IP.
- The web server (Nginx) handles incoming requests and can serve static content directly.
- Dynamic requests are passed on to the application server.
- The application server communicates with the database to fetch or update data.
- The web server compiles the response and sends it back to the user's web browser for display.
